parameters: \N<Hinata Aki> Ah, Taro, you finally came.
\N<Hinata Aki> I was just talking to Nakano-san.

Nakano-san, who lives in the neighborhood, is an elderly man
who lives alone and has a weak back.

Sometimes I feel like he's giving me a lewd gaze, but he's a
friendly and kind old man. It's probably just my
imagination.

\N<Nakano> You shouldn't trouble your cute childhood friend
too much, Taro-kun~

\N<Hinata Aki> Yeah, seriously! Don't trouble your 'cute'
childhood friend like this!

\N<Hinata Aki> You should be grateful to your cute childhood
friend, you know. Geez...
\N<Nakano> You two are still close, huh~

\N<Nakano> ...Oh, it's already this time. I should hurry and
leave or I'll be late...

\N<Nakano> Aki, who used to look like a boy, has grown into
such huge breasts...
\N<Nakano> Are you trying to seduce me...?
\N<Nakano> I will definitely make you mine, Aki...
\N<Neighborhood uncle> Taro, you seem a bit down.

\N<Neighborhood uncle> Taro, don't go out too much at night,
okay?

\N<Neighborhood uncle> Have you found someone to go to the
festival with?

\N<Man from the neighboring town> I want to go back to my
younger days.

\N<Man from the neighboring town> That short-haired girl
from earlier, her breasts were bouncing around...

\N<Man from the neighboring town> Come to think of it,
tomorrow is the festival...
\N<Hinata Aki> It's been a while, hasn't it?
\N<Hinata Aki> Do you have something you need from me?
\N<Nakano> Oh~ Taro-kun, is this an invitation for a date?
\N<Nakano> Tomorrow is the festival at the shrine, right?

\N<Nakano> Taro-kun is mustering up the courage to invite
you.
\N<Nakano> Why don't you go with him?
\N<Hinata Aki> Then let's meet at the shrine tomorrow.
